<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<style>
  {{ font_faces }}
  {{ base_css }}
  @page { size: A4; margin: 18mm 16mm; }
  .page-break { page-break-before: always; }
  .cover { text-align: left; padding-top: 30mm; }
  .kicker { font-family: '{{ tokens.font_mono }}'; text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.15em; font-size: 9pt; color: {{ tokens.coral }}; }
  h1.title { font-size: 34pt; margin: 8px 0 4px; }
  .dial { display: inline-block; padding: 22px 30px; margin: 24px 0;
          background: {{ tokens.coral }}; color: #fff; box-shadow: {{ tokens.shadow }};
          border: {{ tokens.border }}; }
  .dial .num { font-family: '{{ tokens.font_mono }}'; font-size: 46pt; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; }
  .dial .lab { font-size: 9pt; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; }
  h2 { font-size: 18pt; margin: 26px 0 10px; border-bottom: {{ tokens.border }}; padding-bottom: 6px; }
  .yes { color: {{ tokens.coral }}; font-weight: 700; }
  .no { color: {{ tokens.charcoal }}; opacity: 0.55; }
  ul.reasons { list-style: none; }
  ul.reasons li { border: {{ tokens.border }}; box-shadow: {{ tokens.shadow }};
                  padding: 12px 14px; margin: 10px 0; background: {{ tokens.cream }}; }
  ul.reasons li b { font-family: '{{ tokens.font_display }}'; }
  .footer { margin-top: 30px; padding-top: 12px; border-top: {{ tokens.border }};
            font-size: 9pt; font-family: '{{ tokens.font_mono }}'; }
  .lead { font-size: 12pt; }
  .audit-card { background: {{ tokens.sage }}; border: {{ tokens.border }};
                box-shadow: {{ tokens.shadow }}; padding: 20px; margin-top: 14px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="kicker">Antek Automation · AI Visibility Check</div>
  <h1 class="title">{{ company.name }}</h1>
  <div>{{ company.town }}{% if company.sector %} · {{ company.sector }}{% endif %}</div>
  <div class="dial">
    <div class="num">{{ composite }}</div>
    <div class="lab">AI visibility / 100</div>
  </div>
  <p class="lead">{{ headline }}</p>
  <div class="footer">Prepared {{ run_date }} for {{ addressee }}</div>
</section>

<section class="page-break">
  <h2>What we checked</h2>
  <p>We asked {{ engines|length }} AI engines the questions a real customer would
     ask when looking for a {{ sector_word }} in {{ company.town }}. The same
     {{ queries|length }} questions, put to each engine.</p>
  <table>
    <tr><th>#</th><th>Buyer question</th></tr>
    {% for q in queries %}<tr><td class="mono">{{ loop.index }}</td><td>{{ q }}</td></tr>{% endfor %}
  </table>
  <p style="margin-top:12px;">Engines: {{ engines|join(', ') }}.</p>

  <h2>Where you appeared, and where you did not</h2>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Engine</th><th>You appeared</th><th>Score</th></tr>
    {% for row in engine_table %}
    <tr>
      <td>{{ row.engine }}</td>
      <td>{% if row.score > 0 %}<span class="yes">Yes, in some answers</span>{% else %}<span class="no">Not once</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ row.score }}/100</td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </table>
</section>

<section class="page-break">
  <h2>Who is winning instead</h2>
  {% if competitors %}
  <p>These businesses came up when yours did not:</p>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Business</th></tr>
    {% for c in competitors %}<tr><td>{{ c }}</td></tr>{% endfor %}
  </table>
  {% else %}
  <p>No single competitor dominated, which means this space is open. Whoever
     gets their AI visibility right first will own these answers.</p>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>Three plain reasons this happens</h2>
  <ul class="reasons">
    <li><b>Thin entity data.</b> The AI engines do not have a clear, consistent
        picture of who you are, where you work and what you do. Scattered or
        missing details mean they leave you out.</li>
    <li><b>No structured data.</b> Your site does not spell out your services,
        area and reviews in the machine-readable format these engines read
        first, so they lean on sources that do.</li>
    <li><b>Weak citations.</b> The engines cite the businesses that are
        mentioned and linked across trusted local sources. If those mentions are
        thin, you are invisible to the answer.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="page-break">
  <h2>What a full GEO audit covers</h2>
  <div class="audit-card">
    <p class="lead">This check is the headline. The full audit is the plan.</p>
    <p style="margin-top:10px;">A full GEO (Generative Engine Optimisation) audit
       maps every query that matters in your town, scores you against every
       competitor across ChatGPT, Perplexity and Google's AI results, and gives
       you a prioritised list of the exact fixes: entity data, structured data
       and the citations that move you into the answer.</p>
    <p style="margin-top:10px;">Roughly 85% of UK SMEs have zero measurable AI
       visibility. The ones that fix it now get quoted by name for years.</p>
    <p style="margin-top:10px;"><b>Proof:</b> Antek holds 100% Share of AI Voice
       for "ai voice agents andover", measured with Local Falcon.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="footer">
  {{ tokens.company_name }} · {{ tokens.address_lines|join(', ') }}<br>
  {{ tokens.phone }} · {{ tokens.website }}
</div>

</body>
</html>
